summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), particularly resolutions 1493 and 1533,
Reiterating concern over armed groups and militias in Eastern DRC, 
Condemning the illicit flow of weapons into the DRC, 
Taking note of the report and recommendations of the Group of experts,
Noting the situation in DRC continues to threaten international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,
 Reaffirms demands of paragraphs 15, 18, and 19 of resolution 1493;
2. Renews, until 31 July 2005, provisions of paragraphs 20 to 22 of resolution 1493 and all provisions of resolution 1533;
3. Intends to modify or remove these provisions if demands are satisfied;
4. Will review these measures by 1 October 2004, and periodically thereafter;
5. Requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Group of experts within 30 days, expiring on 31 January 2005;
6. Requests the Group of experts to report to the Council before 15 December 2004, on implementation of measures imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493;
7. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
